{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}} {{Use Australian English|date=November 2016}} '''Grant Evans''' (1948&ndash;2014) was an Australian anthropologist and historian notable for his works on [[Laos]].
He received his Ph.D. from [[La Trobe University|La Trobe]] in 1983, and for many years taught anthropology at the [[University of Hong Kong]].
In 2005, he moved permanently to Vientiane, where he was a senior research fellow at the [[École française d'Extrême-Orient]]. He died in Vientiane on 16 September 2014.<ref>[http://www.laos.embassy.gov.au/files/vtan/Prof%20Dr%20Grant%20Evans%201948-2014%20-%20the%20Loss%20of%20a%20National%20Treasure.pdf Obituary] by John Williams, Australian Ambassador to the Lao PDR.</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160305005838/http://www.lowyinterpreter.org/post/2014/09/19/Grant-Evans-1948-2014.aspx Obituary] by [[Milton Osborne]].</ref><ref>[https://www.linkedin.com/today/post/article/20140918143212-4958802-a-researcher-every-country-dreams-of-obituary-dr-grant-evans Obituary] by Lili Sisombat.</ref>
